<br>
I have a question about one of the server rules. Can someone please tell me if you know the exact (or approximate) numbers for penalties and bonuses for grouping with similar or dissimilar alignments? <br>
<br>
For example, the server rule implies there is some bonus if say 2 Orderly Good Paladins and 1 OG Cleric are grouped together, since they are all of same aligments. So what would that bonus be? 10%? 15%? <br>
<br>
I did not see a reference anywhere on these numbers. I appreciate any input. Am thinking of joining this server, as the RP ruleset looks appealing. <br>
<br>
Moandor <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 7:15:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1000.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV alignment grouping penalty/bonus numbers?</span><hr size=1> Verant tends not to release these numbers.  The only reason other numbers of this sort are available is due to long analysing by players with too much time on their hands.  Considering that these bonuses/penalties are unique to FIriona Vie I don't imagine anyone has bothered to properly run the numbers.  But hey, I coul be wrong.<br>
<br>
Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 8:01:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1000.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV alignment grouping penalty/bonus numbers?</span><hr size=1> thanks for responsing Valquiss<br>
<br>
It's a shame Verant wont make these statistics public knowledge. I really wanted to know how much it affected player experience points. I was curious as to how much of a hit they really are when you consider grouping with other players of different alignments, for example a GOOD teaming up with NEUTRALS. My curiosity just wants to know... is it a small tiny hit like 5%? Or is it more drastic like 20%? <br>
<br>
If it's a small tiny hit like 5%, then IMHO it's nothing to lose sleep over.  <br>
<br>
But if it's a large hit like 20%, then it definitely will make me think twice before grouping with anyone outside my race or alignment group. It could possibly alter player behavior, as well as have an indirect affect on role playing behavior on the server. It will certainly have a psychological impact on the server. <br>
<br>
Just speculating.... Im not flaming or critcizing anyone, not even Verant. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 8:51:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1000.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AFAIK...</span><hr size=1> AFAIK Neutrals do not add or detract from bonuses.  It's like adding a 0% bonus.<br>
<br>
EXAMPLES:<br>
<br>
Assume ALL groups in this set up are groups of Three, so add in the group XP bonus.  Class xp penalties only affect the player, not groups anymore (long story, long time ago, it's moot) so we can not really worry about classes.<br>
<br>
Three OG players, say 15% on TOP of the grouping bonus for 3 players.  This is an ARBITRARY number for illustration purposes ONLY.<br>
<br>
Two OG players and one *true* neutral, say 10%.<br>
<br>
Two OG players and one ON, I'm not sure.  Maybe it's 10, maybe it's 15...I've heard bonuses depend on the Order/Chaos variable, not on the Good/Evil variable.<br>
<br>
One OG, one ON, and one OE.  I wonder if it's 15% since they're all order?<br>
<br>
I know orders and discords DO have penalties, probably 5% in this case for One OG, one NG, one DG.  However, the percentage HAS been stated by Verant to be LESS than the grouping bonus.  So there IS a hit, but you're STILL going to get some bonus because it's another body.<br>
<br>
I'd like to stress that.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if goods and evils do, since they're not supposed to group at all (but they can; another story, another board, another thread...) <p>--Antoin &lt;Shadow Dragoon&gt;
<br><i>"I'm glad to report that I'm the only pinnacle of evil in a 30-mile radius."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyntercrystalbow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wynter Crystalbow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 12:50:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1000.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AFAIK...</span><hr size=1> Actually, I read an article on this why they don't release numbers.  It seemed to make Verant seem really evil, but it made a lot of sense.  It's sort of the same reason they don't make the actual xp you earn or need for next level public knowledge.  It's based upon reward vs. effort.  Experience is an unknown quantity, while you know generally in a sense how much experience you get from a kill, you can't keep complete track of it, and can't actually estimate how many more kills you will need to level.  This forces you to keep plugging away, and in many cases keeps you in the dark if another area is substantially better but doesn't show up on your xp meters.  If you knew, you might take a more relaxed pace, or desert some areas, but since you are in the dark, you keep plugging away, trying to beat your way up to the next level like a mouse in some sadistic experiment.  It's a marketing ploy, mainly.  It keeps players connected more to the game since if they knew the actual stats they might possibly become discouraged and leave the game.  Evil, indeed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhueth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hueth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 4:57:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1000.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> IMO</span><hr size=1> Having grouped with Nuetrals and Goods and Orders and Discords, I have to say that my clinical observation is that there isn't a big difference.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't base your decision on the alignment penalty.  The language barrier and sparse population here however, have affected peole more profoundly.  <br>
<br>
All I can say is, &quot;Come on in!  The water's fine!&quot;<br>
